* wal_commit_rollback_regression.dts
* Self-bootstrapping WAL / COMMIT / ROLLBACK durability regression (AIF-041 M1).
*
* Derived from pinocchio/wal_phaseA_proof.dts, but SELF-ASSERTING (machine-checkable
* ".T." markers via the expression path) instead of ECHO/DISPLAY. It creates its OWN
* throwaway x64 table (WALREGR), proves a buffered+logged REPLACE is APPLIED by COMMIT
* and DISCARDED by ROLLBACK, then erases the table. Fixture-free: it never touches the
* shared students table -- the exact bug that made the legacy commit_rollback_test.dts a
* silent no-op (it assumed students was already open).
*
* Environment bootstrap (regression doctrine: every test sets its own environment; the
* ambient default is STOP_ON_ERROR OFF): sets STOP_ON_ERROR OFF + ECHO OFF at its top,
* and points the DBF/INDEXES/LMDB path slots at the SANDBOX area so the throwaway table
* is created there (isolated from live data), not in data\dbf\x64.
* The leading ERASE makes the run idempotent if a prior run left WALREGR behind (ERASE
* of an absent table is a non-fatal "Table not found" while STOP_ON_ERROR is OFF).
*
* Pass criterion: W0, W1, W2 all print ":.T." between the BEGIN and END markers.
*   W0 -> the throwaway fixture built (recno 2 NAME = Beta) via a direct write
*   W1 -> COMMIT applied the buffered+logged REPLACE (recno 1 NAME = Alpha2)
*   W2 -> ROLLBACK discarded the buffered REPLACE (recno 2 NAME still = Beta)
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN WAL_COMMIT_ROLLBACK
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/pinocchio/wal_commit_rollback_regression.dts

SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

* Isolate to the SANDBOX area so the throwaway WALREGR is created under
* data\dbf\SANDBOX, never in the live data\dbf\x64 tree (mirrors sandbox.dts and the
* INDEX_X64 smoke convention). Like the other suite scripts, this test sets its own
* path slots and does not restore them (each test establishes the area it needs).
SET PATH DBF DBF/SANDBOX
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/SANDBOX
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/SANDBOX

FORMULA "WAL-COMMIT-ROLLBACK-REGRESSION-BEGIN"

* --- P0: build a throwaway x64 table with two rows (self-bootstrap; direct writes) ---
ERASE TABLE WALREGR CONFIRM
CREATE X64 WALREGR (ID N(4), NAME C(20))
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "1"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Alpha"
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "2"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Beta"
GO 2
? "W0_fixture_row2_beta:" + (ALLTRIM(NAME) = "Beta")

* --- P1: enable persistent (RAM+JOURNAL) table buffering ---
TABLE BUFFER ON PERSISTENT

* --- P2/P3: buffered+logged REPLACE on recno 1; COMMIT must APPLY it ---
GO 1
REPLACE NAME WITH "Alpha2"
COMMIT
GO 1
? "W1_commit_applied:" + (ALLTRIM(NAME) = "Alpha2")

* --- P4: buffered REPLACE on recno 2; ROLLBACK must DISCARD it ---
GO 2
REPLACE NAME WITH "RolledBk"
ROLLBACK
GO 2
? "W2_rollback_discarded:" + (ALLTRIM(NAME) = "Beta")

* --- cleanup: disable buffer, close, erase the throwaway table ---
TABLE BUFFER OFF
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE WALREGR CONFIRM

FORMULA "WAL-COMMIT-ROLLBACK-REGRESSION-END"
